Here's how to get your FlowPortal code:

Push to GitHub (Recommended)
Click "Save to GitHub" button in the chat interface (top area)
Connect your GitHub account if not already connected
Select your repository and branch
Click "PUSH TO GITHUB" — your entire codebase gets pushed
Then just git clone it on your server.

Deployment on Your Own Server
Once you have the code, here's what you need:

Requirements:

Node.js 18+ (for React frontend)
Python 3.11+ (for FastAPI backend)
MongoDB (local or Atlas)
Backend setup:

cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
# Edit .env with your own values:
#   MONGO_URL, DB_NAME, JWT_SECRET, CORS_ORIGINS
uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8001
Frontend setup:

cd frontend
yarn install
# Edit .env:
#   REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=https://your-domain.com
yarn build    # creates production build in /build
# Serve /build with nginx, caddy, or any static file server
Key .env variables to update:

File	Variable	Set to
backend/.env	MONGO_URL	Your MongoDB connection string
backend/.env	JWT_SECRET	A strong random secret
backend/.env	CORS_ORIGINS	Your frontend domain
frontend/.env	REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL	Your backend URL (must include /api routing)
Default admin login: admin@flowportal.com / admin123 — change this after first login.
